President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring March 18-24, 2018 as National Poison Prevention Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of taking precautions and being prepared for emergency situations to prevent accidental poisonings. It highlights the alarming increase in accidental drug-poisoning deaths, particularly due to opioid overdose, and discusses the efforts made by the administration to combat the opioid epidemic. The proclamation also encourages Americans to safely dispose of unneeded prescription medications and emphasizes the need to store potentially dangerous products out of sight and reach of children. Overall, the proclamation aims to raise awareness about the dangers of unintentional poisonings and urges individuals to take actions to protect their families and prevent injuries and deaths.